** Procedure For Optimization - Diagnosing And Servicing Each Unit **
The Outside Air Temperature Must Be Above 60 Degrees. Do Not Conduct The Optimization If The Oat Is Below This Temp
You Will Be Required To Take Specific Temperature Readings With Your Fluke Or Similar Temperature Probes Clamp On Sensors Work Best For Liquid Line Temp Readings
1. Identify If These Units Are On The 53Rd Bms System Or Not
2. Perform A Physical Inspection Of Equipment And Note Any Issues
3. Fill Out Y/N Equipment Condition Questions And Take Required Photographs
4. Make Sure That The Unit Is Running 100% Cooling Before Taking Temp Readings.
** If The Unit Is On The 53Rd Bms System Use The Feautures In This Survey To Trigger A Timed Override By Raising/Lowering The Space Temperature Readings To Cause Full Cooling Or Heating **
5. Record Measurements As Specified **Before** Any Repairs Are Made
6. Submit/Upload The Diagnostic Form
7. Receive Diagnostic Email - Check Your Email Shortly After Uploading The Survey Form
8. Determine What Repairs Are Needed
9. Repair Equipment Or Submit A Quote For Repairs When Nte Would Be Exceeded
10. After Repairs Are Made Use The Serviceqc Survey Form To Verify That The Units Are Fully Optimzed And Performing Correctly

** If This System Is Not On The 5th 3rd Bms System ** Use The Thermostats To Lower The Temperature Setpoint To Fully Load Unit (100% Cooling).** ** Recommend Dropping Cooling Setpoint Down 4 Degrees On This Unit ** If Unit Is Unable To Command All Stages On, Attempt Manual Pin Or Button Override Test Loading The System To 100% ** Do Not Forget To Reset The Thermostat To It'S Original Setpoint When Finished **

** If This System Is On The 5th 3rd Bms System ** Use The Timed Override Feature Of This Form To Override The Space Temperature (If Kmc Flexsttat ) Or The Cooling Setpoint (If Using A Bacnet Card) To Fully Load Unit (100% Heating) For A Specified Duration ** ** If Flexstat: Set The Space Temp To 75 Degrees And The Unit Will Command All Cooling Stages On For The Duration That You Set ( Make It No More Than 30 Minutes)** ** If Bacnet Card: Set The Cooling Setpoint To 55 Degrees And The Unit Will Command All Heating Stages On For The Duration That You Set. Most Units Have A 45F Oat Lockout ( Make It No More Than 30 Minutes)**
If Unit Is Unable To Command All Stages On, Attempt Manual Pin Or Button Override Test Loading The System To 100%
**Be Advised** The Condenser Panel Needs To Be Shut During All Measurements And All Cooling Stages Must Be On And Unit Cooling At 100%
